OL,4,Cwins payout
OL,6,FShe continued to be paid her
OL,7,F"notional" salary of #9,000 per year,
OL,8,Fbut after Mr Herling spoke to the
OL,9,Fbusiness's accountant, who said his
OL,10,Fwife could not be paid if she was not
OL,11,Fworking for the pub, he issued her
OL,12,Fwith a P45.
OL,14,FMrs Herling was not told about the
OL,15,FP45, which had been issued through an
OL,16,Felectronic payroll system, the
OL,17,Ftribunal was told.
OL,19,FLeft without a salary, she started a
OL,20,Fnew job at a local supermarket, the
OL,21,Ftribunal heard.
