OL,6,FThe tribunal concluded that Mrs
OL,7,FHerling was dismissed on November 4
OL,8,F2022, "when she found out that she had
OL,9,Fbeen issued with a P45".
OL,11,F"An employee cannot effectively be
OL,12,Fdismissed unless or until she is told
OL,13,Fso or has been given notice of such,"
OL,14,Fthe panel said.
OL,16,F"The likely outcome may have been that
OL,17,F(Mrs Herling) would not ultimately
OL,18,Fhave returned to work, but (Mr
OL,19,FHerling) should have tried, at that
OL,20,Fstage, to reach a compromise."
